    "Background": {
      "text": "HSV\ninfection of distal finger\n[1]\nUsually occurs from contact with oral herpes, or autoinoculation from genital herpes\nIncubation period of 2-20 days, with possible prodrome of fever or malaise\n60% due to HSV-1, 40% due to HSV-2",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": [
        {
          "text": "HSV",
          "url": "https://wikem.org/wiki/HSV"
        }
      ]
    },
    "Clinical_Features": {
      "text": "Same burning, pruritic sensation as from other herpes infections\nVesicular bullae\nFinger may be indurated and tender (but should not be tense, as in a felon)\nRash develops over 7-10 days, with possible ulceration and rupture\nSymptoms improve, crust over, and heal after 10-14 days with viral shedding terminating at this point\nComplete resolution by 15-21 days",
      "subsections": {},
      "tables": [],
      "links": []
    },
